üöÄ Burp Suite Quick Setup Guide (Fast Lab Setup)

This guide shows how to set up Burp Suite + Firefox + FoxyProxy for web pentesting and PortSwigger labs.

Goal: intercept HTTPS traffic in under 5 minutes.

üß∞ Requirements

Burp Suite Community or Pro

Firefox browser

FoxyProxy extension

1Ô∏è‚É£ Install Burp Suite

Download:

https://portswigger.net/burp

Run Burp ‚Üí choose Temporary project ‚Üí Start Burp.

Burp will open with the proxy listener enabled by default.

Verify listener:

Proxy ‚Üí Options ‚Üí Proxy Listeners

You should see:

127.0.0.1 : 8080

If missing, add it manually:

Address: 127.0.0.1

Port: 8080

2Ô∏è‚É£ Install FoxyProxy (Firefox)

Open Firefox ‚Üí install extension:

https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/foxyproxy-standard/
3Ô∏è‚É£ Configure FoxyProxy

Open FoxyProxy ‚Üí Add new proxy.

Fill exactly:

Type: HTTP
Hostname: 127.0.0.1
Port: 8080
Username: (blank)
Password: (blank)
Proxy DNS: OFF

Save and turn the proxy ON.

Your browser is now sending traffic to Burp.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Install Burp CA Certificate (IMPORTANT)

Without this step HTTPS will fail.

While proxy is ON, open:

http://burp

Download:

CA Certificate ‚Üí cacert.der
Import certificate into Firefox

Open:

about:preferences#privacy

Scroll ‚Üí Certificates ‚Üí View Certificates ‚Üí Authorities ‚Üí Import

Select cacert.der and check BOTH boxes:

Trust this CA to identify websites

Trust this CA to identify email users

Click OK.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Test Intercept

In Burp:

Proxy ‚Üí Intercept ‚Üí Intercept is ON

Visit any website in Firefox.

If the page freezes ‚Üí interception works ‚úÖ

Click Forward in Burp to load the page.

Burp is now successfully performing HTTPS interception.

6Ô∏è‚É£ Essential Burp Workflow

Daily workflow for labs:

Browser ‚Üí Proxy ‚Üí Send to Repeater ‚Üí Attack ‚Üí Intruder (automation)

Main tabs you‚Äôll use:

Tab	Purpose
Proxy	Capture traffic
Repeater	Manual testing
Intruder	Automated attacks
Decoder	Encode / decode payloads
